criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

        - Generalized neck-shoulder pain with symptoms provoked by neck postures, neck movement, or
        palpation of the cervical musculature.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  any contraindication to manipulation, e.g., positive extension-rotation test;

          -  whiplash injury;

          -  previous cervical surgery;

          -  cervical radiculopathy or myelopathy;

          -  diagnosis of fibromyalgia syndrome;

          -  having undergone spinal manipulative therapy in the previous 6 months;

          -  less than 18 or greater than 65 years of age.
